free propagator .

It remains to compute () in the general case.
This can be done rather explicitly, because this function satisfies in
the large  limit a closed equation, which is the Schwinger-Dyson
equation of the matrix model given by
g ^2 (W^2()+_m^2/^2 ^16+m^2/
